         <abstract>
            <p>The market multiple is highly sensitive to volatility. These empirical results suggest that a permanent 1 percentage point increase in market volatility can, over time, reduce the market multiple by 1.8. Hence, any assessment of market valuation that ignores the impact of volatility on the equilibrium P/E is inherently perilous.</p>
          </abstract>
